included.description:
I did a one year honours research project entitled "Visual Cues for the Instructed Arrangement of Physical Objects Using Spatial Augmented Reality (SAR)".
I developed a system to allow a user to arrange 2D representations of physical objects in a Java Swing program, and have resulting visual cues projected onto real-world objects to instruct the arrangement. 
I tracked the real world objects using OpenGL, C++, fiducial markers and the ARToolKit library. 
I designed ten visual cues and performed a UX study to determine the best visual cues for this scenario.
